parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, or in some cases, catch on fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the ignition switch will not return to the run position
the key will not turn
the vehicle's accessories (such as tail lights
brake lights
and turn signals) will not function
the ignition switch catches on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to crank but not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The engine cranks but refuses to start
the vehicle will not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the ignition system can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The ignition switch catches on fire
a fire starts after parking the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Brake lights do not turn on or are intermittent
brake lights only turn on when extreme pressure is applied to the brake pedal
brake lights remain on even when the brake pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Brake lights do not turn on or are intermittent
brake lights only turn on when extreme pressure is applied to the brake pedal
brake lights remain on even when the brake pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop running, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stalls or loses power while driving
often without warning
and may not restart immediately. The engine may die or shut off
and the vehicle may lose all power
including electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty TFI module can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
often without warning
and may not restart immediately. The TFI module may need to be replaced
but the problem may persist even after replacement.
